reply_text:
@blozzjani Hmm.... You are aware that Star Wars wasn't actually filmed in space and there is no such place as Mordor; I'm no expert but I think they built sets to meet story requirements. 🤷‍♀

And did you the read the bit that it was "based on an international bestseller" not just the characters? How did you manage to finish the book if you couldn't even read those few words? You wouldn't set Miss Marple on Mars (or Centre Parcs!!!). 

And if you want to use a straw man argument to discuss adaptations of source material how are the Marvel films doing these days? I think you'll find moviegoing audiences are more sophisticated than you give them credit ... but fortunately this is literally a made-for-TV film so moviegoers won't need to trouble themselves.
